A `Proxy` is a substitute for a singular container aka [`Scalar`](https://docs.perl6.org/type/Scalar). A `Hash` is a plural container where each element is by default a `Scalar`.

A possible solution (based on [How to add subscripts to my custom Class in Perl 6?](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/36773986/how-to-add-subscripts-to-my-custom-class-in-perl-6/36785245#36785245)) is to delegate implementation of `Associative` to an internal hash but override the `AT-KEY` method to replace the default `Scalar` with a `Proxy`:
```
class ProxyHash does Associative {

  has %!hash handles
    &lt;EXISTS-KEY DELETE-KEY push iterator list kv keys values gist Str&gt;;

  multi method AT-KEY ($key) is rw {
    my $element := %!hash{$key};
    Proxy.new:
      FETCH =&gt; method ()       { $element },
      STORE =&gt; method ($value) { $element = $value }
  }
}

my %hash is ProxyHash;
%hash&lt;foo&gt; = 42;
say %hash; # {foo =&gt; 42}
```

